{"ts":"2026-05-17T08:59:44.986Z","author":"codex-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"Implementation direction:\n- Extend PmSettings with agent_guidance state and defaults in src/types.ts and src/core/shared/constants.ts.\n- Extend settings schema, merge, and serialize ordering in src/core/store/settings.ts; keep output deterministic.\n- Add init option wiring in src/cli/register-setup.ts and action schema optional keys in src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts.\n- Update help text in src/cli/help-content.ts and JSON/help payload expectations so agents discover the later-add path.\n- Consider a read/reset config key only if implementation needs an operator escape hatch beyond pm init --agent-guidance add/skip/status. If added, keep scope project-only and document clear behavior.\n- Keep MCP pm_run init schema in sync through SDK contracts so connected agents can request guidance add/status without shell-specific assumptions."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-b8rf"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Expose agent guidance init option in settings, contracts, help, and config"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Make the new pm init agent-guidance behavior discoverable and machine-safe across settings schema/types, runtime help, SDK contracts, MCP action schema, and optional config inspection."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":1},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","contracts","help","init","pm-cli","sdk","settings"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-05-17T08:59:44.986Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-05-17T08:59:44.986Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"codex-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"settings schema accepts and persists agent_guidance deterministically; pm init help and JSON help include the guidance option; pm contracts --command init --flags-only and action schema expose the option; MCP schema can pass the option; config/docs give a clear operator path to inspect or reset declined state if implemented."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-7t04"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-7t04","kind":"parent","created_at":"2026-05-17T08:59:44.986Z","author":"codex-agent"},{"id":"pm-8rjn","kind":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-17T08:59:44.986Z","author":"codex-agent"}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-05-17T08:59:44.986Z","author":"codex-agent","text":"Child task created from pm-7t04. This slice makes the UX contract visible to humans and agents after prompt behavior exists."}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"aa832e56c38bb1a3d2096ce50d74e0c165718b2e337bed480903ffe4d6477669","message":"Create child task for contracts help and settings surfaces"}
